Born on June 4, 1991 in Cleveland, Ohio, Olivia was a talented gymnast from an early age. She began training at the age of just five and showed potential at national level competitions throughout her childhood.

Olivia joined the UCLA Bruins gymnastics team for college after winning various junior competitions as well later went on coach younger athletes at a local gym in California.

In late-2020, she released her memoir "Falling into Place," detailing her journey as an elite gymnast and sharing some of the experiences that many athletes face behind closed doors. The book quickly became a New York Times bestseller and garnered significant attention for its honest account of the extreme pressure young athletes can experience while competing at high levels.

Unfortunately, tragedy struck when Olivia's life took a turn for the worse after suffering physical injury while performing daredevil stunts in Los Angeles.
